cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on using natural language inference (NLI) models for fake news classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses machine learning models such as BERT, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with cybersecurity and fake news, which suggests the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
